# Cockpit → Control UI: Full 1:1 Consumption & Rebrand Spec

> **Status**: Complete migration. The Cockpit **consumes** the built-in Control UI 1:1 — all abilities, settings, routes, and components — rebranded under Cockpit's oklch theme token system.
> **Constraint**: NO new parallel implementations. Reuse Control UI source code directly. Rebrand only.

---

## 1. Executive Summary

The Control UI is a full Gateway management dashboard embedded in the OpenClaw gateway. The Cockpit is a standalone static build. This spec mandates **complete consumption**: the Cockpit imports Control UI source modules directly, preserving all functionality while applying Cockpit's visual identity (oklch hue-cycling, dark-first, shadcn/ui primitives).

**Golden Rule**: If the Control UI already does it, import it. Do not rewrite it.

---

## 2. Consumption Strategy

### 2.1 Source Code Location

**⚠️ CRITICAL FINDING**: The `~/.openclaw` repository does NOT contain a `ui/` directory with Control UI source. The repo only contains runtime data (agents, sessions, config, logs, etc.).

The Control UI source must be obtained from the **upstream OpenClaw repository**:

```bash
# Clone the upstream OpenClaw repo (separate from ~/.openclaw runtime data)
git clone https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw.git ~/openclaw-source
cd ~/openclaw-source
# The Control UI source is typically in: packages/ui/ or apps/control-ui/
```

**Alternative**: The Control UI is also available as built assets in the npm package:
```
~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.2/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/control-ui/
```

However, these are **minified production builds** — not importable source modules.

### 2.2 Consumption Options (Ranked)

| Option | Viability | Effort | Notes |
|--------|-----------|--------|-------|
| **1. Iframe embed** | ✅ Best | Low | Load `/control-ui/index.html` in iframe, theme via postMessage |
| **2. Upstream source clone** | ✅ Good | Medium | Clone `github.com/openclaw/openclaw`, import from `packages/ui/src` |
| **3. Reverse-engineer API** | ⚠️ Fallback | High | Use gateway RPC types, rebuild UI from scratch |
| **4. Decompile built assets** | ❌ Bad | Very High | Minified chunks are not practical to consume |

### 2.3 Recommended: Iframe Embedding

The fastest path to 1:1 functional parity:

```typescript
// components/cockpit/ControlUiEmbed.tsx
export function ControlUiEmbed({ route }: { route: string }) {
  const iframeRef = useRef<HTMLIFrameElement>(null);
  const { mode, hue } = useCockpitTheme();

  useEffect(() => {
    // Inject theme into Control UI via postMessage
    iframeRef.current?.contentWindow?.postMessage({
      type: 'cockpit-theme',
      mode,
      hue,
    }, '*');
  }, [mode, hue]);

  return (
    <iframe
      ref={iframeRef}
      src={`/control-ui/index.html#/${route}`}
      className="w-full h-full border-0"
      style={{
        // Apply oklch overlay to blend with Cockpit shell
        filter: mode === 'dark' ? 'none' : 'invert(1) hue-rotate(180deg)',
      }}
    />
  );
}
```

