## 4. Theme Token Integration (Rebrand Rules)

### 4.1 oklch Override System

All consumed Control UI components receive theme context via a **CockpitThemeProvider**:

```typescript
// lib/theme-provider.tsx
import { createContext, useContext } from "react";

const CockpitThemeContext = createContext({
  mode: "dark", // "dark" | "light" | "system"
  hue: 0,       // 0-360 for oklch cycling
  pulse: "idle", // idle | streaming | error | offline
});

export function ThemeWrapper({ children }) {
  const theme = useContext(CockpitThemeContext);
  return (
    <div data-cockpit-theme={theme.mode} data-cockpit-hue={theme.hue}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4.2 CSS Custom Property Injection

```css
/* styles.css — injected into consumed Control UI components */
[data-cockpit-theme="dark"] {
  --control-bg: oklch(15% 0.02 var(--cockpit-hue));
  --control-fg: oklch(95% 0.01 var(--cockpit-hue));
  --control-accent: oklch(70% 0.2 var(--cockpit-hue));
  --control-error: oklch(60% 0.25 25); /* red hue fixed */
  --control-warn: oklch(75% 0.18 85);  /* orange hue fixed */
}

[data-cockpit-theme="light"] {
  --control-bg: oklch(97% 0.01 var(--cockpit-hue));
  --control-fg: oklch(15% 0.02 var(--cockpit-hue));
  --control-accent: oklch(60% 0.2 var(--cockpit-hue));
}
```

